<p>Templates provide a great deal of flexibility in your promotions, but serve to provide consistency across all university communications. The template you use depends upon the nature of your communication, your audience, and where you will display your message. There are three categories.</p>
<h1><span style="font-size: medium;">L1-University Formal</span></h1>
<p>Description:</p>
<ul>
<li>Reserved for official university messages</li>
<li>Messages are formal in nature</li>
<li>Used most often for off-campus formal communication</li>
</ul>
<p>L1 is for reserved for departments, colleges, and offices wishing to  communicate fundamental messages off campus. Examples include:  Communication from the the Executive Office, or peices to be displayed  in Institute buildings.</p>
